[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"i need a summer camp or summer enrichment opportunity for my 13 yr old daughter in Manhattan for Summer 2026 . are there programs that teach vocational skills or S.T.E.M for 13yr olds Summer 2026 STEM & Vocational Programs for 13-Year-Olds in Manhattan Knowledge Base Document Created: Summer_Camp_Research_2026_v1 Executive Summary Great news — Manhattan has excellent STEM and vocational programs for 13-year-olds. I've compiled the most reputable options with application timelines, costs, and skill outcomes. Key insight: Applications for competitive programs open October 2025 - February 2026, so you're timing this research perfectly. Top Programs Comparison Table Program\tFocus Area\tDuration\t2025 Cost (Est. 2026)\tApplication Opens\tKey Skills Output\tSelectivity Girls Who Code Summer Immersion\tCoding, CS\t2-6 weeks\tFREE\tJanuary 2026\tPython, Web Dev, App Development\tCompetitive (apply early) iD Tech Camps @ NYU/Columbia\tCoding, Game Dev, AI, Robotics\t1-week sessions\t$1,299-$1,899/week\tOpen now (rolling)\tPython, Java, Unity, AI/ML basics\tOpen enrollment Columbia Engineering Summer Program\tEngineering, Robotics\t2-3 weeks\t~$3,500-5,000\tFebruary 2026\tEngineering design, CAD, robotics\tModerate Marymount Summer STEM\tScience, Tech, Engineering\t2-4 weeks\t~$2,000-3,500\tMarch 2026\tLab skills, coding, engineering\tOpen enrollment NYC Parks Summer STEM Programs\tEnvironmental Science, Tech\t6-8 weeks\tFREE\tApril 2026\tEnvironmental science, data analysis\tLottery-based Parsons School of Design - Pre-College\tDesign + Tech, UX/UI\t2-4 weeks\t~$3,000-4,500\tJanuary 2026\tDesign thinking, prototyping, UX\tPortfolio review Bank Street Science Camp\tHands-on Science/STEM\tMulti-week\t~$1,800-2,500\tFebruary 2026\tScientific method, experimentation\tOpen enrollment Cooper Union Summer Art/Engineering\tArt + Engineering intersection\t2-4 weeks\t~$2,000-3,500\tFebruary 2026\tDesign, CAD, fabrication\tPortfolio/application Vocational-Focused Options (Real-World Skills) Program\tVocational Skill\tLocation\tCost\tOutcome The Beam Center\tFabrication, woodworking, electronics\tBrooklyn (near Manhattan)\t~$1,500-2,500\tBuild real projects, power tools certification MakerSpace NYC Youth Programs\t3D printing, laser cutting, CNC\tVarious Manhattan\t~$500-1,200\tPortfolio of fabricated items NYC Youth Design Studio\tArchitecture, urban design\tManhattan\tFREE (application)\tDesign portfolio, city planning skills Digital Media Academy\tVideo production, content creation\tNYU Campus\t~$1,800/week\tYouTube-ready video editing skills Application Timeline Flowchart Copy ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │                    APPLICATION TIMELINE 2025-2026                    │ ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │                                                                      │ │  OCT 2025          JAN 2026           MAR 2026          MAY 2026    │ │     │                 │                   │                 │        │ │     ▼                 ▼                   ▼                 ▼        │ │  ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐       ┌──────────┐      ┌──────────┐  │ │  │ Research │───▶│ Apply to │──────▶│ Apply to │─────▶│ Confirm  │  │ │  │ & Prep   │    │ FREE/    │       │ Paid     │      │ Enrollment│ │ │  │ Daughter │    │ Competitive│      │ Programs │      │ & Payment │ │ │  │ Interest │    │ Programs  │       │          │      │           │  │ │  └──────────┘    └──────────┘       └──────────┘      └──────────┘  │ │                                                                      │ │  ★ Girls Who Code: JAN deadline                                      │ │  ★ Columbia/Cooper Union: FEB deadline                               │ │  ★ iD Tech: Rolling (book early for preferred dates)                │ │  ★ NYC Parks: APR lottery                                            │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ Recommended Action Plan (SOP) Step\tAction\tClick-by-Click Instructions\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTimeline 1\tAssess Daughter's Interests\tSit down and discuss: Coding? Building physical things? Science? Design? Content creation?\t15-min conversation\tRanked list of 2-3 interest areas\tThis week 2\tRegister for Girls Who Code Alerts\tGo to girlswhocode.com → Programs → Summer Immersion → Click \"Notify Me\" → Enter email\tEmail address\tConfirmation email when apps open\tThis week 3\tCreate iD Tech Account\tGo to idtech.com → Click \"Create Account\" → Browse summer 2026 dates at NYU → Save favorites\tBasic parent info\tAccount with saved program options\tThis week 4\tBookmark Columbia Engineering\tGo to precollege.sps.columbia.edu → Set calendar reminder for Feb 2026\tCalendar app\tReminder set\tThis week 5\tApply to FREE Programs First\tGirls Who Code + NYC Parks = $0 cost, high value\tApplication essays, school info\tApplication confirmations\tJan-Apr 2026 6\tSubmit Paid Program Deposits\tAfter acceptance to free programs, decide on backups\tPayment method\tSecured spot\tMar-May 2026 Cost-Optimization Strategy Strategy\tRationale\tPotential Savings Apply to Girls Who Code FIRST\t100% free, teaches Python + web dev, NYC location\t$2,000-5,000 NYC Parks STEM lottery\tFree citywide programs, environmental focus\t$1,500-2,500 Use iD Tech early-bird pricing\t10-15% discount for early registration\t$200-300 Check school scholarship portals\tMany programs offer need-based aid (apply separately)\t25-100% My Top 3 Recommendations Based on your profile (digital business owner, course creator, content focus): Girls Who Code Summer Immersion — FREE, teaches Python/web development, could lead to her building sites or apps for your ventures long-term Digital Media Academy at NYU — Video production and editing skills directly applicable to YouTube content creation (synergy with your work) The Beam Center (Brooklyn) — Hands-on fabrication/maker skills; teaches real-world problem-solving, unique portfolio projects Next Steps — What I Need From You What are her current interests? (Coding? Physical making? Science? Video? Design?) Budget range? (Free only, under $2K, flexible up to $5K?) Preferred duration? (1-week intro vs. 6-week intensive?) Once you answer, I'll narrow this to a shortlist of 3 with direct application links and a week-by-week action calendar. Document saved to Knowledge Base: Summer_Camp_Research_2026_v1 — will update as we refine options. create the live URL links for all the free resources/ can budget $2k but prefer free Updated Summer 2026 STEM & Vocational Programs — Live URLs Added Knowledge Base Updated: Summer_Camp_Research_2026_v2 FREE Programs (Priority Tier — Apply First) Program\tFocus\tLive URL\tAge Eligibility\tDuration\tApplication Window\tKey Skills Output Girls Who Code Summer Immersion\tCoding, CS, Web Dev\tgirlswhocode.com/programs/summer-immersion-program\tRising 9th-12th grade (13 eligible if rising 9th)\t2-6 weeks\tJanuary - March 2026\tPython, HTML/CSS, JavaScript, sisterhood community All Star Code Summer Intensive\tCoding for boys of color + all genders now\tallstarcode.org\t14-18 (check for 13yr eligibility)\t6 weeks\tFebruary 2026\tWeb development, entrepreneurship pitch Mouse (NYC-based)\tCS + Design Thinking\tmouse.org/programs\tMiddle/High school\tVaries\tRolling\tApp design, circuitry, creative tech NYC Ladders for Leaders\tPaid internship (career exposure)\tnyc.gov/ladders\t14-24 (she's 1yr early — bookmark for 2027)\t6 weeks summer\tJanuary 2026\tProfessional skills, stipend SYEP Summer Youth Employment\tCareer exposure + paid\tnyc.gov/syep\t14-24 (1yr early — bookmark)\tSummer\tFebruary-April lottery\tPaid work experience NYC Parks Urban Fellows / STEM\tEnvironmental STEM\tnycgovparks.org/opportunities\tVaries by program\t6-8 weeks\tApril 2026 lottery\tEnvironmental science, conservation Microsoft TEALS / DigiGirlz\tTech exposure days\tmicrosoft.com/en-us/diversity/programs/digigirlz\tMiddle/High school\t1-day events\tOngoing\tExposure to tech careers Google CS First\tSelf-paced coding\tcsfirst.withgoogle.com\tAll ages\tSelf-paced (free)\tAlways open\tScratch, block coding, animation Khan Academy Computing\tSelf-paced coding\tkhanacademy.org/computing\tAll ages\tSelf-paced (free)\tAlways open\tJavaScript, SQL, HTML/CSS Codecademy (Free Tier)\tSelf-paced coding\tcodecademy.com\tAll ages\tSelf-paced\tAlways open\tPython, JS, HTML — foundational The Knowledge House (Bronx/NYC)\tTech + career\ttheknowledgehouse.org\t16+ (bookmark for later)\tMulti-week\tRolling\tWeb dev, career readiness Under $2,000 Programs (Backup Tier) Program\tFocus\tLive URL\tCost (Est.)\tDuration\tApplication\tSkills Output iD Tech Camp @ NYU\tCoding, AI, Game Dev\tidtech.com/locations/new-york-summer-camps/nyu\t$1,299-$1,599/week\t1-week sessions\tRolling (open now)\tPython, Roblox, Unity, AI The Beam Center\tFabrication, building\tbeamcenter.org\t~$1,200-1,800\tMulti-week\tFeb-March 2026\tWoodworking, electronics, power tools MakerSpace NYC\t3D printing, CNC\tmakespace.nyc\t~$500-1,000 (workshops)\tVaries\tRolling\tDigital fabrication NYSCI (NY Hall of Science) Camps\tHands-on STEM\tnysci.org/camps\t~$500-900/week\tWeek sessions\tMarch 2026\tScience experiments, engineering Marymount Summer\tSTEM Academy\tmarymountnyc.org/summer\t~$1,500-2,000\t2-4 weeks\tMarch 2026\tCoding, robotics, science 92Y Summer Camps\tTech + creative\t92ny.org/camps\t~$1,200-2,000\tMulti-week\tFeb 2026\tMixed media, tech, arts Visual Application Priority Funnel Copy ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐ │         FREE PROGRAMS               │ │     ★ APPLY TO ALL OF THESE ★       │ └─────────────────────────────────────┘ │ ┌───────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┐ ▼                           ▼                           ▼ ┌───────────────┐          ┌───────────────┐          ┌───────────────┐ │ Girls Who Code│          │   Mouse NYC   │          │  NYC