ledge Base Updated: Summer_Camp_Research_2026_v3 — Pre-College Prep Addendum Executive Summary Pre-college programs that accept 13-year-olds are less common than 14+ programs, but they exist. I've identified programs across three categories: university-sponsored, test prep/academic enrichment, and specialized STEM/arts pipelines. Many elite programs start at 14, so I've included those with \"bookmark for 2027\" notes where relevant. University-Sponsored Pre-College Programs (13-Year-Olds Accepted) Program\tUniversity\tLive URL\tAge\tCost\tDuration\tFocus Areas\tApplication Opens Johns Hopkins CTY Summer Programs\tJohns Hopkins\tcty.jhu.edu/programs/summer\t8-16 (grade-based)\t$2,000-6,500\t2-3 weeks\tMath, science, writing, CS — requires qualifying test scores\tDecember 2025 Duke TIP Summer Studies\tDuke\ttip.duke.edu/programs/summer-studies\t7th-10th grade\t$2,500-5,500\t2-3 weeks\tSTEM, humanities, leadership\tJanuary 2026 Northwestern CTD Summer\tNorthwestern\tctd.northwestern.edu/summer-programs\tGrades 4-12\t$1,800-5,000\t1-3 weeks\tEnrichment across subjects\tFebruary 2026 Columbia Pre-College Programs\tColumbia NYC\tprecollege.sps.columbia.edu\t14+ only\t$3,500-12,000\t1-3 weeks\tBookmark for 2027\t— NYU Pre-College\tNYU\tnyu.edu/admissions/high-school-programs\t14+ (rising 10th)\t$3,000-6,000\t2-4 weeks\tBookmark for 2027\t— Barnard Pre-College\tBarnard\tbarnard.edu/precollege\t14+ (rising 9th-12th)\t$3,500-8,000\t2-4 weeks\tSTEM, writing, leadership\tBookmark for 2027 CUNY College Now\tCUNY System\tcuny.edu/academics/k-12/college-now\t9th-12th grade (check age)\tFREE\tSchool year + summer\tEarn college credits\tRolling Prep for Prep\tMulti-university pipeline\tprepforprep.org\tStarts 5th grade (pipeline)\tFREE\tMulti-year\tLeadership, college prep\tGrade 5 entry — may be past window Gifted/Talent Search Pre-College Pipelines (Qualify by Test) These programs require qualifying scores on SAT, ACT, or their own assessments. Strong pathway to university recognition. Program\tSponsoring Org\tLive URL\tAge/Grade\tCost\tHow to Qualify\tBenefits Johns Hopkins CTY\tJHU\tcty.jhu.edu\t2nd-12th grade\tTest: $50 / Programs: $2K-6K\tScore 95th+ percentile on qualifying test OR take CTY's own test\tAccess to advanced summer courses, credential for college apps Duke TIP\tDuke\ttip.duke.edu\t4th-10th grade\tTest: $55 / Programs: $2K-5K\tScore 95th+ on qualifying test\tTalent search recognition, summer programs, online courses Northwestern CTD\tNorthwestern\tctd.northwestern.edu\tK-12\tVaries\tAssessment or school nomination\tGifted programming, weekend/summer enrichment Davidson Institute\tDavidson\tdavidsongifted.org\tK-12 (profoundly gifted)\tFREE\tApplication + documentation of giftedness\tScholarships, mentorship, community Art of Problem Solving (AoPS)\tAoPS\tartofproblemsolving.com\tMiddle/High school\t$200-500/course\tSelf-select\tAdvanced math, competition prep, online community NYC-Specific Pipeline Programs (Many FREE) Program\tFocus\tLive URL\tAge\tCost\tApplication\tWhy It Matters Prep for Prep\tLeadership + elite school placement\tprepforprep.org\tStarts 5th grade\tFREE\t5th grade entry\tPipeline to Ivy League, mentorship through college A Better Chance (ABC)\tAcademic placement\tabetterchance.org\tMiddle school start\tFREE\tApplication\tBoarding school placement, college prep Oliver Scholars\tCollege prep for students of color\toliverscholars.org\t7th grade entry\tFREE\t7th grade application\tSAT prep, college counseling, enrichment TEAK Fellowship\tIntensive college prep\tteakfellowship.org\t7th grade entry\tFREE\t7th grade (may be past window)\t10-year support through college Minds Matter NYC\tMentoring + college prep\tmindsmatter.org/nyc\t10th grade start\tFREE\tBookmark for 2028\tSAT prep, mentorship, college visits Breakthrough NYC\tTeaching + college prep\tbreakthroughnyc.org\t7th-8th grade\tFREE\t7th grade entry\tSummer academic enrichment Sponsors for Educational Opportunity (SEO Scholars)\tCollege prep for underserved\tseoscholars.org\t9th grade entry\tFREE\tBookmark for next year\t8-year program through college Academic Test Prep & Enrichment (13-Year-Olds) Program\tFocus\tLive URL\tCost\tFormat\tOutput Kaplan Young Scholars\tSAT/PSAT intro, study skills\tkaptest.com\t$500-1,500\tIn-person + online\tTest strategy, score improvement Princeton Review PSAT Prep\tPSAT fundamentals\tprincetonreview.com/college/psat-test-prep\t$400-1,200\tVarious formats\tNational Merit pathway awareness Kumon\tMath/reading mastery\tkumon.com\t~$150-200/month\tWeekly centers\tGrade-level advancement Art of Problem Solving\tAdvanced math\tartofproblemsolving.com\t$200-500/course\tOnline\tCompetition math, develops problem-solving Khan Academy Official SAT Prep\tSAT practice\tkhanacademy.org/sat\tFREE\tSelf-paced online\tLinks to College Board, personalized practice Decision Matrix: Which Path Fits Your Daughter? Copy ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │                    PRE-COLLEGE PROGRAM DECISION TREE                        │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐ ▼                               ▼ ┌─────────────────┐             ┌─────────────────┐ │ Academically    │             │ Wants hands-on  │ │ gifted / high   │             │ skills, not just│ │ test scores?    │             │ academics?      │ └────────┬────────┘             └────────┬────────┘ │                               │ ┌──────────┴──────────┐         ┌──────────┴──────────┐ ▼                     ▼         ▼                     ▼ ┌──────────────┐      ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ │ TALENT SEARCH│      │ PIPELINE     │ │ STEM CAMPS   │ │ VOCATIONAL   │ │ Johns Hopkins│      │ PROGRAMS     │ │ Girls Who    │ │ Beam Center  │ │ Duke TIP     │      │ SEO, Oliver  │ │ Code, iD Tech│ │ MakerSpace   │ │ Northwestern │      │ TEAK, Prep4P │ │ (See v2 doc) │ │ Fabrication  │ └──────────────┘      └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ │                     │                │                │ ▼                     ▼                ▼                ▼ Requires test         Most require      Open enrollment   Open enrollment qualification         earlier entry     Apply Jan-Mar     Apply Feb-Apr (SAT/ACT/CTY)        (5th-7th grade)   2026              2026 Programs She Can Still Enter at 13 (Not Too Late) Program\tWhy Still Accessible\tAction Required\tDeadline Johns Hopkins CTY\tGrade-based, not age-locked\tTake qualifying test (SAT, ACT, or CTY assessment)\tRolling, but summer app by Feb Duke TIP\t7th-10th grade eligible\tTake qualifying test\tJan-Feb 2026 Northwestern CTD\tK-12 eligible\tApply for summer\tFeb 2026 Oliver Scholars\t7th grade entry — check if 8th grade cohort exists\tContact directly\tDecember 2025 Breakthrough NYC\t7th-8th grade\tApply now for Summer 2026\tDecember-January Girls Who Code\tRising 9th-12th grade (she qualifies)\tApply January 2026\tMarch 2026 Tactical SOP: Pre-College Prep Application Strategy Step\tAction\tClick-by-Click Instructions\tInput\tOutput\tTimeline 1\tAssess if talent search is right fit\tHave daughter take practice PSAT at khanacademy.org/sat → Review score\t2-hour test time\tBaseline score to determine CTY/TIP eligibility\tThis week 2\tRegister for Duke TIP talent search\tGo to tip.duke.edu → Click \"Talent Search\" → Create account → Register for 7th grade search\tParent/student info, $55 fee\tOfficial talent search recognition\tDecember 2025 3\tRegister for JHU CTY\tGo to cty.jhu.edu → Click \"Talent Search\" → Register → Schedule qualifying test\tParent/student info, $50 fee\tCTY eligibility, unlocks summer programs\tDecember 2025 4\tContact Oliver Scholars directly\tGo to oliverscholars.org/contact → Email to ask if 8th grade entry exists\tEmail explaining daughter's background\tResponse on eligibility\tThis week 5\tApply to Breakthrough NYC\tGo to breakthroughnyc.org → Click \"Apply\" → Complete application\tApplication, school info\tSummer 2026 admission decision\tDec-Jan 2026 6\tSet calendar for 14+ programs\tAdd reminders: Columbia Pre-College (Jan 2027), NYU (Jan 2027), SEO Scholars (Fall 2026)\tCalendar\tReady for next-year apps\tToday Cost Comparison Summary Tier\tPrograms\tEstimated Cost\tValue Proposition FREE\tOliver Scholars, TEAK, Prep for Prep, SEO, Breakthrough, Girls Who Code, CUNY College Now\t$0\tPipeline programs, mentorship, long-term support Low Cost\tDuke TIP/CTY talent search registration\t$50-55\tOpens access to recognition + summer programs Under $2,000\tDuke TIP summer, Northwestern CTD 1-week, AoPS courses\t$500-2,000\tUniversity-level enrichment, credential building $2,000-5,000\tJHU CTY residential, Duke TIP residential\t$2,500-5,500\tImmersive experience, top-tier university affiliation My Top Recommendations for Your Daughter Based on age (13), timing (Summer 2026), and budget preference (free first): Immediate Actions (This Month) Contact Oliver Scholars — Free, NYC-based, supports students of color through college. Check 8th grade entry. Apply to Breakthrough NYC — Free summer academic program, still accepts 7th-8th graders. Register for Duke TIP or JHU CTY Talent Search — $50-55 unlocks recognition and summer program access. Even if she doesn't attend summer program, the credential looks great on applications. Summer 2026 Applications (January) Girls Who Code — Free, teaches Python + web development, strong for college apps. Duke TIP or Northwestern CTD Summer — If budget allows, 2-week residential academic immersion at university. Bookmark for 2027 (When She's 14) Columbia Pre-College, NYU Pre-College, Barnard Pre-College — Opens at 14. SEO Scholars — 9th grade entry, free 8-year program through college. Questions to Narrow Down Has she taken any standardized tests recently? (Scores help determine CTY/TIP eligibility) Is she interested in residential programs (living on campus 2-3 weeks) or commuter only? What's her strongest subject? (Math/science → CTY science track; Writing/humanities → Duke TIP humanities; Tech → Girls Who Code) Should I draft outreach emails to Oliver Scholars and Breakthrough NYC using your Gmail access? Knowledge Base Updated: Summer_Camp_Research_2026_v3 — Pre-College Prep Programs Added we lice in Harlem so anythign based in New York is preferred but she is already in a boarding school so she can travel and be away it needed Updated Pre-College Prep Programs — Harlem Base + Boarding School Flexibility Knowledge Base Updated: Summer_Camp_Research_2026_v4 — Harlem Local + Residential Options Executive Summary This changes the strategy significantly — great news. Since she's already at boarding school, she has: Independence and maturity for residential pre-college programs (big advantage) Flexibility for programs outside NYC Harlem location opens access to strong local pipeline programs specifically serving Uptown Manhattan I've reorganized into: Harlem/Uptown Local, NYC-Wide, and National Residential options. Harlem & Uptown Manhattan Programs (Walking Distance/Local) Program\tFocus\tLive URL\tLocation\tAge\tCost\tApplication\tWhy It Matters Harlem Educational Activities Fund (HEAF)\tCollege prep, leadership, mentorship\theaf.org\tEast Harlem (E 124th St)\t6th-12th grade\tFREE\tRolling\t12-year pipeline through college, strong alumni network Brotherhood/Sister Sol (BHSS)\tLeadership, social justice, college prep\tbrotherhood-sistersol.org\tWest Harlem (W 143rd St)\t8-22 years old\tFREE\tRolling\tIntensive youth development, summer programs Harlem Children's Zone\tComprehensive college prep\thcz.org\tCentral Harlem\tBirth-college\tFREE\tBy zone/application\tWraparound support, Promise Academy connection Apollo Theater Education Programs\tArts + STEM integration\tapollotheater.org/education\t125th Street\tMiddle/High school\tFREE - Low cost\tRolling\tPerformance, media production, unique portfolio Dance Theatre of Harlem Summer Intensive\tDance + discipline\tdanc